title: Goldrausch
description: Stephan helps a forest heiress arrange management, suddenly aided by nature's bounty which caused the taxable problem in the first place. Wolfgang sells his 'valuable Canadian gold-prospection experience' to unsuspecting tourists. His plan to fake a find proves costly in more then one unexpected way. Stephan teaches Mr. Göbe how to handle a virtual step-son. Daniel reports his silly step-sister missing.

title: Hoch gepokert
description: Wood trader Markus Rombach's firm is falsely rumored to be in financial trouble, which may cause real problems. In fact Küblach's forestry cooperation manager Hubert Gassner is gambling away his and the society's capital at cards. Stefan Leitner discovers everything and tries to calm the victims. The girls meanly taunt Daniel while he suffers from bad influenza. Greedy bickering over lotto winnings becomes Jozef and Wolfgang badly.

title: Liebesbeweis
description: Forester Stefan worries about a rogue horse rider, who ignores the rules about accessible forest paths. The mere suggestion of introducing municipal horse ID chips makes owners suitably alert. Jozef and Wolfgang try to rid the father Amlbos's church organ of its squirrel nest. The rider causes an accident. Stefan solves both problems.

title: Gefangen auf Teneriffa
description: Stefan takes his lover Sonia along on a business-holiday trip to the Canary island Tenerife. He visits his ex, vet Nathalie Kamp, in the local zoo, but she's mean commissioner Puerta's main suspect for the theft of a chimpanzee baby. Shortly after, Nathalie's hunky lover, Julian König, attempts the next robbery, eggs of a lizard species near extinction. Sonia is in his way, so he has to kidnap her and fails to get the eggs. Julian has to tell his dad, dodgy tycoon Raphael König, who fears the buyer, Carlos, enough to blackmail Stefan.

title: Verbockt
description: Stefan's stepson Daniel's years of model behavior seem to end, feeling deeply hurt because the girls get undeserved treats while he is stuck with endless chores. Stefan sees it's rather unfair but offers only to pay for extra allowance the hard work, which only seems to increase Dani's bitterness. Farmer Hans Sailer's adult son Ferdinand has bought a water buffalo to produce Küblach mozzarella, a promising novelty, but the bovine escapes and causes damages all over the village. Wolfgang clumsy ruins his wedding, which attracted a Candian surprise guest, Indian chief Singing Bear. After more trouble, Daniel's deepest grief is revealed: his real dad Karsten is emigrating to Greece.

title: Das liebe Geld
description: A nightly storm cause great damage in the forest and some houses, notably Leitner's roof. Stefan feels guilty for having spent his savings on a dream-horse, his only indulgence amidst limitless sacrifice for his (step)family. Yet when Jenny finds out, she even 'overrules' his wise handling of 'her' children. Daniel resents being the only family-member being 'called to order' for an evening hanging out with mates. Wolfgang needs an occupation,so Stefan puts him in charge of replace the village may (tree), which task he takes too seriously. The forestry laborers bicker who may go on an exchange to Canada.

title: Teamwork
description: Kümlach is threatened by an epidemic of bark beetles, which could kill off its forest unless it's handled jointly. Even spoiled brat Lisa realizes it's unfair Daniel is the only sibling without a treat, so when his PC breaks down she offers him her piggy-bank, having no use for cash. That convinces step-dad Stefan to offer Dani a deal: he'll pay the rest for help fighting the beetles. Young Ferdinand Sailer gets dad Hans's blessing, at Stefan's recommendation, to fight the beetle for their family, and helps save the whole town.

title: Katz und Maus
description: Küblach is in danger of being infested by rabbits, who could eat the young tree shoots. Stefan hosts the Canadian exchange forester. Instead of his experienced friend Stephen, it's a charming youngster, Tom 'TK' Keller, whose cute looks instantly seduce Stefan's teenage daughter. Tom's 'imagination' wins over the men. Wolfgang blames 'negligent doc' Sonja when Joeph gets mysterious allergic symptoms after visiting both of them.

title: Geplatzte Träume
description: Stefan vehemently opposes Jenny's intention to seduce the hunky, young adult Canadian exchange forester Tom 'TK' Keller, who never gave her any cause to believe he feels more then courteous friendship for her. The girls meanly gang up against Daniel because he's amused to see the brat (16) feeling haunted for a chance. Stefan realizes first why TK couldn't by interested in Jenny: he's gay. Wolfgang seems the only adult in Kübach who isn't worried the neighboring town wants to steal 'his' may tree as revenge for his triple stunt, but actually he's cunningly prepared for them.

title: Radikalkur
description: Küblach can get a good deal to use expensive forestry equipment, but only if everyone joins in. Only Laura Bergmeister, who inherited her father's farm and stubbornly insists to prove her worth, refuses, the latest of a serious of aberrations from time-honored practices her father wisely adhered to, thus antagonizing everyone, in the end even her lover Ferdinand. Stefan has to make her see reason. He also comes up with a brilliant idea after Sonja, Wolfganga and Marianne fail to convince Joseph he's not ill but suffering from hypochondria.

title: Schwein gehabt
description: Daniel entered a raffle to win an mp3 player, but got a 'miniature' piglet, which all three kids want to keep. Stefan must find and catch it, then convince them cute piglets become huge swine. The vicar heads the opposition when the mayor considers a lucrative project for Kublach municipality: a 'rest wood', or cemetery in a forest track, which Stefan must assess. Binder is back from Canada and resuming forestry duty with bis mates.

title: Hitzewelle
description: It has been scorching hot in Küblach for weeks, so even Stefan dives into the pool on the job. Daniel has joined the truants, Steff, Mark and Tobias, who made him drink alcohol and even vandalize public property. Wolfgang needs a cheap birthday gift for Marianne, so Jozef offers to pick up his ancestral right to harvest river clam pearls. When they find the river so low it threatens the mollusks, Wolfgang turns ecologist, but his dam threatens Kreidtmayr's trout farm. Once more, Stefan must pull his step-don and dad back in line and solve the water shortage.

title: Urlaubsplanung
description: Daniel and Lisa get a surprise visit form their father, Karsten, who wants to take them to his new Greek home a few weeks during the summer holiday. Forgetting to notify Marianne who was to pick them up at school cause an excessive scene and search, but Stefan accepts to help them make up. Sonja felt side-tracked, especially now Stefan allows his daughter Jenny to visit her ma's grave in her natal Canada, but Stefan buys her dream-ring. Wolfgang has started auctioning wood he bough far cheaper from the municipal wood, so people suspect Stefan of nepotism. Stefan worries more about amateurs using chainsaws, knowing the gruesome bloody risks.

title: Zapfenstreich
description: During her kids' Greek holiday with dad Karsten, Stefan plans to propose to Sonja. He tells only Marcus, who swears silence but can't deny when his wife Anna guesses, and she spills the beans to Sonja, while both lovers's professional emergencies mess up their romantic evening plans. Meanwhile Stefan's expert eye for maples spots unacceptable foreign breed seedlings. Wolfgang's next scheme is a crazy countryside casino, based on cow droppings.

title: Brautschau
description: Stefan mediates when conflicting interests concerning walking and riding requires equipping a new path for horse-rides. He's seduced into enjoying another ride on his ex-horse Tango, but the owner steals a kiss when he gallantly helps her down. Sonja acts viciously jealous, but the real reason delights him. Wolfgang has posted a contact advert for Joseph. The desirable bachelor is not amused when four dubious suitors turn up, complete baffled when the last proves to be his ex Gerlinde, who left him and filed for divorce for years ago, yet insists to honor her motel booking.

title: Fieberhafte Suche
description: Stefan teaches the primary school kids about the forest by organizing a treasure hunt. His own kids are back from abroad, Daniel sad to leave his summer lover behind and anxious the baby may be another girl. Wolfgang is ecstatic about the first visit in 20 years from Stefan's godfather, uncle Ludwig, Dr. Mehringer, but can't deal with him suffering from advanced Alzheimer. Pregnant Sonja keeps working with the flu despite fainting, until Ludwig sends her to hospital, where Dr. Lechner diagnoses serious Q-fever, highly contagious but only from sheep. Stefan tirelessly searches for the culprit flock, and finds it at a scary place.

title: Geheimrezept
description: Sonja is back from hospital and found healthy, as well as the baby, whose position in the center of parental attention renders selfish Jenny nastily jealous. Stefan has a hard time convincing the locals to help him collect forest path data for a GPS system to help outsiders such as lumber truckers. Hermann Koller has started smoking his own deer meat for the local Ochsen inn. Shortly after the tasting by forestry colleagues, both get food poisoning, but Sonja and Stefan have a hard time figuring out what the poison is.

title: Raubtiere
description: Both small animals and shiny objects go missing all over Küblach. Stefan ends up discovering two kind of somewhat excusable thieves, ravens and a would-be-zoo-keeper. Sonja tried long to hide their engagement ring was among the loot, but is even treated to a repeat-proposal. Ferdinand has had it with has impossible to please dad, and leaves the ancestral home. Laura soon accepts to let her lover move in as farm partner. Moritz feels pushed away, but soon discovers his agricultural experience offers alternative options.

title: Familiengeheimnis
description: Stefan is puzzled when a local forest exploiter refuses to sell a tract for a great price because it's 'not his to dispose of'. It turns out Marianne's late husband Franz's illegitimate son's education was paid from its proceeds, and now he's famous he wants to buy it. Stefan's brat daughter brought a 'stray' deer calf home, and returning it to the mother is problematic as the crucial scent has been wrecked.

title: Attentat
description: A single shot out of the blue leaves groom Stefan unconscious, bleeding from a head wound in the forest. It takes an hour until Joseph and Wolfgang find him and get him hospitalized, but luckily there is no lasting damage. Indignant newcomer Bachhofer waves Wolfgang's insinuation that his gun collection fits the ammo used. Josef helps recovering Stefan investigate whether there's a connection with apparent hare poaching.

title: Lukas kommt!
description: Now Stefan is fully recovered, the church is booked again to prevent baby Likas being born out of wedlock, but during the service he decides otherwise. Daniel is atypically silent, seemingly uninterested, while the girls shirk the inevitable extra domestic chores. Stefan helps the small farmer who accidentally shot him with trouble over the sale, for lack of other assets, of his drought horse to a rich neighbor, who claims it's no good.

title: Endlich Hochzeit
description: The Leitner family must adapt now baby Lucas and his mother arrive from hospital. Only Daniel isn't jealous of all the attention given to the youngest sibling, the girls however turn away indignant. On top of extra chores, Daniels volunteers to earn enough for a driving course by taking daily meteorological measurements. However an opportunity to driver mate Kurt's absent big brother's cool car is irresistible, Stefan finds out and cancels the deal. Curate Ambrose agrees to organize Stefan's third attempt to marry in secret, with a hot air balloon.

title: Sturmschäden
description: Daniel surprises everyone by earning the fee for his driver's license by mucking out cattle stables for a grumpy farmer. A storm causes lots of work in the forest tracts. Old Breitkreuz breaks a leg when knocked off his ladder by the impatient aforementioned farmer's tractor, which Daniel works out. Stefan seeks to prevent hospitalized Breitkreuz being fired by Bachhofer.

title: Winkelzüge
description: The village shivers due to an enterprising youth campaign against drunk driving after a bad accident. Daniel finally has saved up for his driver's lessons, but the chilling image of his sister nearly killed makes him loose his calm, so Stefan builds his confidence up again. Tailing a fox to his hole leads Stefan to the spot where the debris from Bachhofer's villa renovation must have been illegally dumped. The schemer denies and manages to sell that piece of land with 10 years usufruct, creating a legal accountability quagmire. Josef thinks he stumbled on Wolfgang having an affair in Passau, but it's just tango lessons.

title: Erpressung
description: Daniel's former girlfriend Vanessa (16) suddenly moves into the youth hostel, pregnant. After speculations and tension about paternity, she admits he's not the father but the only boyfriend she can trust. To Stefan's surprise, the charms of the mayoress, who further neglects her family, seem to persuade Max Bachhofer to withdraw his plans for construction on a forest tract. Instead he proposes to donate it for a nature reserve, provided Stefan and two other farmers throw in their neighboring parcels. The Lietner family counsel accepts.

title: Fehltritte
description: Stefan discovers beaver activity requiring tree-protection and must tread carefully when a valuable natural wood oddity goes missing, only to be discretely returned. Daniel is not amused when pressed to be there for Vanessa, but Stefan accidentally discovers her father and finds him far more understanding then she claimed. Wood merchant Markus Rombach is startled when his wife Anna suddenly renounces her plan to stand for another mayoral term, out of guilt over an adulterous night with Max Bachhofer.

title: Beweisführung
description: Stefan's staff must map and fight a plague of beetles, but a grumpy farmer misuses the traps. While Daniel is on model behavior, his brat sister Jenny exhausts Stefan's patience by letting her grades slip, party every night and be caught with drugs. Curate Ambrose presents her to former addict Björn, crippled for life. Josef minds a retired cop's sniffer dog, so Wolfgang concocts lucrative schemes, and discovers he can actually smell the pest beetle. Anna tells Markus she's renouncing another mayoral term, not why, but the tension remains, so she ends up confessing her adultery with Bachofer.

title: Für und Wider
description: Stefan discovers a maize bug epidemic, proving once more the dangers of monoculture, and works out it spares a single plot in Bachhofer's fields because of genetic manipulation, but fails to keep that secret before protests raise, with Josef and the publican he has a crush on as ringleaders. The Bavaraian ministry supervisor wants Stefan to mediate. He motivates the mayoress to use her romantic influence to make Bachhoofer destroy the field, but the rising marital tension in her household ends with her leaving Stefan's buddy Markus and taking his beloved son David away. Daniel and sister Lizzie get only half heir school trip's fee, provided they raise the rest. Wolfgang is obsessed with finding out how Marianne's goats keep escaping their pen, requiring tiresome mustering from the fields.

title: Treibjagd
description: Stefan invites his depressed mate Markus Rombach, who is bitter because wife Anna's adultery was kept from him, to move in with the Leitners for a few days, not expecting he would turn up immediately. So Sonja, who plans to reopen her medical practice, wasn't even told and finds Marcus a rather demanding guest. Max Bachhofer engaged a new personal assistant to help organize a posh 'pheasant battue' for business relations. Stefan is expected to keep the peace and implores the hostile villagers to provide the required beaters, but only Josef can convince them by devising a vile plot, which even causes the accident Stefan tried to prevent. Stefan and his dog distract young David, who misses daddy Marcus as much as the other way around.

title: Vollgas
description: Stefan educates the local farmers about how to react to the rising bio-gas-plants' lucrative demand for cereal growers byproducts. After a towel-down incident, Marcus realizes he's overstaying his welcome and moves out of the Leitner home, clearing the way for Sonja to prepare for her medical praxis reopening, while Marianne volunteers to mind the girls regularly. Finding a list of 'things to do', Wolfgang assumes it's buddy Joseph's and organizes one item, a dangerous ride with an agricultural machine, ignoring the actual list author.

title: Aus heiterem Himmel
description: Stefan gets fed up with Sonya's unwillingness to have sex months after Lucas's birth but the real shock is her ultimate confessions he's not the biological father. A wounded buzzard proves meanly aggressive. Curate Ambrose makes Wolfgang pay in charitable kind for the next listed dream, a macho motorbike ride.

title: Freier Fall
description: Stefan is starting to deal with the shock that little Lucas isn't his biological son, but unlike him Sonya won't put their kids first and decides cowardly to move, even sees a buyer for her practice behind his back. Stefan must concentrate first on a Czech gang of dog-nappers after his trusted Sina becomes their latest victim right under his eyes while inaugurating the village's new horse riding course. Wolfgang struggles to find enough courage for Josef's extra-list dream, a parachute jump. To Stefan's horror, Sonya left him and took the children with her to a Passau house, even unwilling Daniel.

title: Wüste Küblach
description: Stefan is miserable, having lost his family by Sonya's cowardly flight. Wolfgang and Joseph bizarrely prevent Marianne from feeling the same by being among many local victims of an epidemic. The village's most urgent problem, possibly the root cause, is a leak in the water-works. Stefan rightly suspects the leak is in an outdated pipe, but has to fight his forestry colleague and superior to get proper equipment used. A lady veterinarian passing by meets Stefan in unfortunate circumstances, but they get on remarkably well.

roles.char: Notar und Rechtsanwalt Dr. Alois Gerstner

title: Hals über Kopf
description: The mayor of Störzing am Ammersee makes unemployed forester Stefan an offer he can't resist: run their fine forest and a nature reserve he'll be in charge of setting up. The mayor bluffs about 'other candidates who already accepted' to get Stefan's yes the same day. Still, he dreads telling the home front, especially his wife Marie, who can take over a retiring GP's practice in their old village.

title: Ins kalte Wasser
description: Now Stefan has accepted his new forester job, he must urgently move to his official residence in Störzing. The male relatives help, son Daniel even drops by from college, while his sister just wines and her cat seems to hide near the old home. Worst is Stefan's wife Marie, who still plans to take over a medical practice there, but her sister makes her see sense.

title: Kräftemessen
description: Now Stefan is moving, the home front prepares grudgingly to put his house on the market to be rented the next 10 years, but clumsy dad and his mate cause a barn fire hazard. The victim's fatherless daughter bullies and robs his yellow daughter. Stefan discovers a wood trade irregularity involving his forestry assistant. Marie finally decides to leave Küblach but drags out moving.

title: Das Geheimnis im Moor
description: Stefan has to take in his dad, Wolfgang's buddy Josef and their former host Marianne after her homestead B&B is consumed in a fire started in the barn. Amid all the wining and practical arrangements, Stefan can hardly concentrate on an urgent quarterly report. Still he reacts instantly to a report that a corps, probably some 200 years old, is found in the moor by the traditionalist turf-harvester and his warning it's being wrecked by drying, so Stefan urges the mayor the municipality must stop the milk cattle ranchers' neighboring contracts and include the bog in the nature reserve project. Back home, his old but best forester is fired.

title: Zwischen den Stühlen
description: Stefan is delighted to discover an eagle's nest, but must risk intervening because plastic used to build it ruins the drainage. A failure would also compromise his plans for the nature reserve, which are opposed in the municipal council by the milkery owner who secretly builds a regional monopoly. She conspires with disgruntled forestry assistant Ronny' Badstuber, promising bribery. The insurance is only prepared to pay out 80,000 Euros, claiming the fire was the result of carelessness bordering on arson. Wolfgang, Josef and Marianne now consider a smaller home, but Stefan offers to sell his 'inhertitance' home so they can get a proper estate again, perhaps near his new home.

title: Entscheidung aus Liebe
description: Stefan discovers that foxes are dying without exterior lesions, has it checked out scientifically and thus learns he must search for a poison-monger. Meanwhile his touchy foreman practically chucks in his job, but Stefan finds it's on account of his daughter, who is dying from a mystery virus he assumes to stem from foxes. Wolfgang, Joseph and Marianne decide to settle in Störzing so they can remain with Stefan. Marie keeps whinging about her veterinary career slump.

title: Ein verlockendes Angebot
description: Stefan examines the case of shot foxes, but the mayor makes his only evidence, a bullet, disappear. The wicked milker plant owner's plan to make the last farmer in the way sign over the Gebauer land works, but her heir Konstantin refuses to cooperate because he doesn't want the family firm. Stefan is far from pleased about Marie's secretive, selfish attitude when her ex Michael offers her a job as his veterinary practice partner.

title: Bauchgefühl
description: To Stefan's delight, forestry student-son Daniel is back home, to do his practicum, but expects to fail his theoretical exams and considers dropping out, only he can't bring himself to burst peacock-pride dad's bubble. Stefan hesitates whether to promote Roland on account of seniority or Eva for her forestry diploma, but ultimately gives the foreman job to his experienced Kublau man Franz Breitkreuz. Stefan promised to deliver a huge quantity of wood, but the only road is blocked because of a careless cross-country motor-biker, whose identity is as shocking as ironical. Wolfgang, Joseph and Marianne fin it hard to square different preferences for a new joint home, but ultimately agree to run the municipality's youth hostel.

title: Ausgebremst
description: Stefan and Gammerdinger worry about roadkill, such as another wild boar on the nature reserve access road, where Konstantin Grandl injures his arm racing in his sports-car. The mayor is reluctant to propose road obstacles which MrS. Grandl is likely to oppose in council. The elderly trio must instruct the architect how to renovate the youth hostel, but the the couple's growing frustration Joseph seems to pull out, as turns out needlessly delicately. Marie's frustration over professional inactivity starts sorting out itself.

title: Verloren gegangen
description: A storm causes major damage in Stefan's nature reserve, and the major doubts if the municipality can put up the necessary funds timely. Bullying by spiteful, jealous Badstuber, whose side Stefan seems to take, makes Daniel's cup flow over, so he decides to run away after Stefan found out he bailed out of college. The Hamburg-based Petersen couple and their daughter, who can't handle their impending divorce, get lost shortly, but end up inspiring Stefan with a great idea: A forest appreciation center. Joseph and Wolfgang each have another purpose in mind for the youth hostel's dependency, so they try to bribe Marianne.

title: Komische Vögel
description: Stefan objects to the mayor's deal to build a road cheaply, using his staff and materials paid for by Grandl, which he proves to be of inferior quality. Stefan and Gammerdinger also deal with four nandus (South American ostriches) that escaped from local Leo's farm just after Marie became his veterinarian, causing havoc all over town. Joseph panics about his hearing after a mishap with furniture delivery for the youth hostel.

title: Unter Druck
description: Stefan and Xaver find an abandoned farm on the natural reserve. It may prove crucial in fighting back when Grandl tries to make the financially overstretched municipal board scrap the project indefinitely. Meanwhile the mayor pursues his affair with Marie's sister.

title: Sina
description: Stefan's trusted canine companion and year-long family pet Sina's off behavior forces Marie to confirm with conclusive tests the dog has terminal cancer, but the Leitners need time to accept the inevitable. The youth hostel's new neighbor uses a legal loophole to circumvent the ban on fences around his forest plot, where he practices "reiki", a Japanese medication and healing technique, which Wolfgang tries out. Mayor Kögl's next courting move leads to an equestrian misunderstanding.

title: Rückkehr
description: Justice assigns some adolescents to the forestry station for community service. They are lodged in the youth hostel and Stefan assigns Daniel to supervise them. However the cocky lads won't accept a good boy's authority just because superiors say so.

title: Wettkampffieber
description: Grandl dairy sponsors the town's annual dog sled race, starring former national champion Thomas Anger. Heir Konstatin however, who has an eye on Lisa, entered into a bet leading to sabotage him. Stefan, who proves himself a born dog handler, is persuaded to take over. Local champion Toni Ramsauer is crucial to the next bet phase. Stefan finds a positive pregnancy kit and worries why Marie didn't tell him, but his daughter Jenny is the expectant one.

title: Von Menschen und Mäusen
description: Stefan doesn't share Marie's optimism that Konstantantin, not even being the biological father, will stand by pregnant Jenny, as the overprotected brat does so far. Stress mounts as the opening of the forest experience center approaches, but it may have to be called off when the illegal waste dumping Stefan's new dog helps discover is found contaminated with Hanta virus. That's transmitted by rodents, and the seniors are just desperately trying to get rid of a mouse in the youth hostel.

title: Seite an Seite
description: The forest experience center's financing is dubious after the town lost its quarry income. The mayor is delighted when a foundation offers to help, but Stefan's mistrust may justified as Grandl's scheming faction is probably behind it. Daniel finds practically free lodgings on site for his training with lonely farmer Paula. After Jenny's miscarriage, the adults doubt if Konstantin will stand by her, but mother's allowance blackmail drives him to move out and seek a place with Jenny.

title: Irrwege
description: Stefan remains more optimistic then his staff about the already delayed opening of the forest experience center. An early guest is a blind one, testing how accessible the facilities are for the handicapped. Alas, her guide dog is diagnosed gravely ill. Bickering Josef and Wolfgang failed to mind young Lucas, whom Stefan finds with the blind girl. Guiding her trough the forest later proves even harder. Mayor Kögl now aspires cohabitation.

title: Nächtliche Besucher
description: Camping in the forest with some mates, Daniel gets a campfire visit from what seems a vagrant wolf and is unable to prevent Henry spreading the news. Stefan delegates the logging course, with only female pupils, to capable seducer Daniela and coarse old Franz, who each have an admirer among them. Stefan tracks the canine down, afraid hunters may kill it first. He identifies it as a Czech dog species and finds the young owner. Meanwhile junior son Lucas gets forgotten.

title: Verspieltes Vertrauen
description: The Bavarian ministry has delivered special permits and ordered the mayor to host a Saudi prince on diplomatic visit, who exceptionally may take home a European buzzard egg. Stefan's protestations are waved and he must cancel his marital quality time weekend, only to learn on site there's very little to do. Stefan ends up in bed with wife Marie's sister Daniela. Daniel finally convinces Petra they should stop hiding their affair, only to find her daughter Anja already guessed and doesn't mind. Stefan however accidentally catching them in the raw and makes a scene he soon regrets. Badstuber is falsely suspected of stealing the other eggs after accepting a 'bribe' from the prince's German agent.

title: Am Abgrund
description: Major foundation sponsor Meierhof makes the major force Stefan to show him around the park, then doesn't show up and 'delegates' to his adolescent sons: Philip, the company heir who returned home from his US college, and irresponsible Anton. Ronald is to take care of them, but can't allow climbing or mountain-biking. Anton decides on the second anyhow, and chasing them, Ronald makes a bad fall, only Philip sees to his rescue. Meanwhile only Daniel truly stands by Stefan after he confessed his infidelity to Marie, who moves out, while the major dumps her unfaithful sister Danielle and is tempted to bury Stefan in work.

title: Eiszeit
description: Wolfgang and most of the villagers keep bugging Stefan about his break-up with Marie, who plans to leave town. Daniel supports Stefan, but that causes trouble with brat sister Lisa who sides with mother without knowing what happened and stays for a while with Petra's daughter Anna, who tempts her to try a dangerous hallucinogenic 'herbal tea'. Stefan wonders if the mysterious affliction of Xaver's bees is on account of grumpy neighbor Franz Berhammer. The veterinary diagnosis is an unrelated parasite, but Stefan does discovers the man's secret contacts with Grandl and the foundation.

title: Aus der Bahn geworfen
description: Stefan meticulously instructs which trees to fell. Yet a branch coming down from another just above a public bench wounds his father who noticed it just in time to prevent it smashing one of the kids he and Josef were showing around and teaching about the forest. A raccoon running wild is caught by old Franz, who hooks up with an initially hesitant lady and tries out living together. Stefan and his forestry team work out who removed his felling mark and why, a case of love. Yet Daniel nor the mayor can convince him to tell and save his job after the ministry threatens to transfer him to its Hq administration. By chance, the culprit is hears about his unjust predicament.

title: Gänsealarm
description: Nearly everyone in Störzing feels miserable. Stefan remains sharply watched by the Forestry department and his family situation is very tense. The mayor painfully fails to avoid his feisty wife. Lake tourism is harassed by wild geese, which prove hard to chase. A falconer is unwisely called in behind Sefan's back. Josef and Marianne can't handle the youth hostel repairs viz. guests in comfortably rehabilitating Wolfgang's absence, yet he seems unmotivated to return home.

title: Heilungsprozesse
description: While fetching a stick, Kai's pet dog is fatally stabbed by a wild boar. Stefan is ordered to mount a driver hunt as the father has clout in town council and ministry. Konstantin is fed up with Jenny giving her journalism academy exam preparation priority over him, yet celebrates generously. The mayor inspires the vindictive women to consider making up with Stefan like he tries. Wolfgang is released from hospital but Josef has a hard time motivating him to pull his weight again rather then linger in bed. Stefan and Badstuber find brat Lisa's animal rights action outright dangerous.

title: Molkerei in Gefahr
description: Stefan expected much-needed funding fro the nature reserve from sponsoring, but the bio-milk Grandl launches is exposed using dodgy cattle-feed by the local paper and activists. Konstantin learns his mother's firm may be bankrupted and thinks up a way out by founding a daughter firm. The bank refuses sufficient credit, but Stefan points out a farmers family looking for an opportunity. Wolfgang, now on crutches, tries to make him self useful but only clumsily bothers Josef and Marianne.

title: Schädlinge
description: Stefan can only commiserate with a small, uninsured local timber grower who is loosing everything, due to a mysteriously appeared Asian citrus tree parasite. It's ultimately traced to Keppler's garden center, run by Eva's romantic partner. Gammerdinger builds an Alpine cabin for free for the nature reserve but gets a naughtily good deal when Grandl and her council ally want the rights to copy and commercialize it.

title: Glückspilze
description: Stefan and Marie accept, surprise, to be witnesses at the wedding of the mayor and Daniella, which becomes public and subject to conspiratorial surprises after the mayoral secretary overhears the couple over the Intercom. Gammerdinger gives a course on mushroom picking and consumption, but Danielle ignores his warning against combining alcohol with a species she took home. Wolfgang and Josef fish trout and sweat over suits for nothing.

title: Katzenjammer
description: A fungal infection affects many young ashes in Störzing's forest, causing danger. Grandl get a municipal council majority for lumbering, but Stefan consults a professor who warns the resistant old trees are the only solution. The school requires Stefan's parental signature in all matters. Martin and the guests bitterly regret him accidentally having inspired Marianne to resume violin lessons.

title: Wut im Bauch
description: An archer terrorizes Störzing's forest wildlife. Constable Tobias Stammberge is powerless, but enjoys catching up with deputy forester Eva, a school friend, rendering her colleague Ronald Badstuber jealous. Daniel graduated with honors, but mayor Kögl regretfully notifies the town can't afford hiring the exemplary apprentice for at least a year. the knave is shocked to hear not only his proud father but even his girlfriend insist he should rather consider better job offers in northern Germany. The mayor's partner Daniela is blackmailed by her ex Harald who knows her stud farm is build on fake pedigrees.

title: Spielverderber
description: Daniel has aced his forestry studies. However the local job he hoped for won't be available for a few years due to municipal budget cuts. He's not amused that father and even lover suggest he should leave town if accepted for better positions in northern Germany. Harald Königstein is back and wants his ex, mayor's wife Daniela, to pay him from the stud-farm proceeds, or he'll wreck it with a secret even she ignored. Sefan's spoiled-rotten daughter Lisa proves an even worse brat on her birthday, declining a traditional party and wining when her buddy Anna snaps up the boy she has a crush on too during the scavenger hunt Stefan painstakingly arranged.

title: Schafskälte
description: The Leitners mourn Marie's sister Daneile, who died while diving alone. Stefan even suspects foul play, but thus widowed mayor Peter Kögl calls a police marker only to find it was a mere accident. Georgios, an unemployed Greek immigrant shepherd, airhead animal-fan Lisa's latest hero, finds his grazing route obstructed by Grandl's private forest management.

title: Machtspiele
description: Konstantin assures his green wood processing firm partner Wolf they can go ahead before they have they required woodland, but his mother seeks Harald's advice and refuses. Stefan's family is shocked that Marie's sister Danielle's testament doesn't make the mayor sole heir of the stud-farm, half of which goes to her ex Harold, who denies earlier agreements. Martin and Lisa take point in the resistance against industrialist Haller's project for a golf course in Störzing, which would destroy valuable otter habitats. Stefan soon realizes only a positive alternative stands a chance after the municipal council's approval, and seeks inspiration with green businessmen Konstantin and Wolf, whom he can offer enough wood.

title: Illusionen
description: To Stefan's astonishment, green mate Xaver is living in an abandoned mobile home, unable to pay the rent after 15 years of dream rate, actually a stealth-compensation for Grandle's father dirty trick to steal the patent on an invention Xaver did while employed in the milk firm as biologist. Stefan and Marie help mayor Kögl save her sister Danielle's stud-farm, but an equine virus exposes him to crippling damages. Harald offers to pay if the farm is transferred to him. Classmate Kai saves Lisa when she faints during a cycling trip from anorexia.

title: Hundstage
description: The nature reserve efforts can finally start paying off: the adventure trail is ready. Stefan personally leads a company's 'team building' party of three, who are unwilling to part even with cellphones. Stefan refuses to help their boss with his real purpose, selecting one of the trio for a promotion. The forestry assistants who came along must face the questions whether they are rivals or lovers. An accident changes the corporate competitors' minds more then anyone expected.

title: Ende gut, alles gut?
description: Dared by a cocky colleague, the mayor needs a female partner in the 'forestry Olympics'. Stefan can't make it, getting bogged down in the surprise mountain retreat he arranged to propose to Marie. Instead she falls asleep and they can't look away when a stroll puts them on the trail of a contagious mountain goats disease, which threatens the painstakingly reintroduced population. Ronald and Eva can't concentrate on the logger-jack games, wrestling with whether to commit, but end up going all the way in bed.
